%I A397503 #12 Jul 13 2026 00:26:59
%S A397503 6,36,90,318,744,1752,1938,1992,5328,10290,36192,46698
%N A397503 Area of the smallest convex polygon (by area) which can be triangulated into n noncongruent Pythagorean triangles.
%H A397503 Charles L. Hohn, <a href="/A397503/a397503.pdf">Example illustration of a(10)</a>
%e A397503 a(1) = 6: a 3,4,5 triangle.
%e A397503 a(2) = 36: a 3,4,5 and a 5,12,13 triangle adjoined at their sides of length 5, in any orientation.
%e A397503 a(3) = 90: 3,4,5, 5,12,13, and 9,12,15, oriented such that the polygon sides are ordered 3,13,9,15,4.
%o A397503 (PARI) \\ see Hohn link in A396266, using require_primitive_triangles = 0 and require_convex_polygon = 1.
%Y A397503 Cf. A396490 (primitive triangles only), A397502 (allowing simple polygons).
%K A397503 nonn,more,new
%O A397503 1,1
%A A397503 _Charles L. Hohn_, Jun 28 2026
